	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 22nd 1:20 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>390 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.26]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I definately have to agree about AoE spells on wisp island, it is suicide! Those spiders LOVE to gang up on people. If you be careful you won't pull more than one wisp ever. My plan of attack was always to pull a single one down to the beach on the far side of the island, and fight it there. If you see two next to each other just wait for them to separate. If you just can't get the hang of it though, and are having too much troubles, then just try some of the other spots I suggested for level 8, ie. the solo siren spawn in OOT or Steamfont.<br><br>Former Everquest Addict that Hopes to Return Soon.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
